reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, Sleek, Efficient
reviews.reviewText: I really like this. We got this one because my husband never looks at his mail and I’m tired of finding it all over, so now I put it here and he must take it with him before he goes to work (lol). It’s also nice because it helps ensure that we don’t forget little things before leaving the house.I like the number of hooks, and they are wide enough that even if we do run out of space (which we haven’t), we could always double up.The paint job is really nice and it looks more expensive than it is. The gold hooks don’t look cheesy at all either, it all goes together very well and is an excellent accent piece.Also, what I really love about it is that there is space on the back for screws & they could fit thumb tacks too. This is great for people in apartments who don’t have command strips on hand and don’t want to screw real screws into a wall.I just used two command strips and it’s held up really well. So so sturdy. Can’t beat for the price.
